*In-depth device and firmware breakdown: http://hckohwnotes.blogspot.de/ :The circuit board has ready-to-solder pins for a serial interface: :4 pads, on the battery side, +Vcc TTL on the square pad, then Txc, then Rxc, then Gnd. :A TTL voltage level (3.3V) to serial (5V), or more commonly USB port adapter such as CP2102 -based plugs, is needed.
*The default port configuration is: 576008N1, software flow control. :The booting log is dumped on this interface, which is then available for logging in through a standard getty.
